
[1]drunkenness

   DRUNKENNESS, n.

   1. Intoxication; inebriation; a state in which a person is overwhelmed
   or overpowered with spirituous liquors, so that his reason is
   disordered, and he reels or staggers in walking. Drunkenness renders
   some persons stupid, others gay, others sullen, others furious.

   Let us walk honestly as in the day; not in rioting and drunkenness.

   2. Habitually ebriety or intoxication.

   3. Disorder of the faculties resembling intoxication by liquors;
   inflammation; frenzy; rage.

   Passion is the drunkenness of the mind.
